[49m[38;5;9m- 95    [0m:[38;5;9m[49m **Amazon SageMaker for model hosting.** The quality assessment model (whether a CNN classifier or a multi-metric pipeline) needs to run inference with low latency and scale with imaging volume. SageMaker real-time endpoints give you managed model hosting with auto-scaling. For the sub-second latency requirement, a SageMaker endpoint with a GPU instance (or an optimized CPU instance for simpler models) is the right choice. You train the model on SageMaker as well, using your historical PACS rejection data as labels.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Amazon SageMaker for model hosting.** The quality assessment model (whether a CNN classifier or a multi-metric pipeline) needs to run inference with low latency and scale with imaging volume. SageMaker real-time endpoints give you managed model hosting with auto-scaling. For the sub-second latency requirement, a SageMaker endpoint with a GPU instance (or an optimized CPU instance for simpler models) is the right choice. You train the model on SageMaker as well, using your historical PACS rejection data as labels. For production deployments handling PHI, enable network isolation on the SageMaker endpoint (`EnableNetworkIsolation=True`) to prevent the model container from making outbound calls.
